       int _barrier_spin_destroy(barrier_spin_t *barrier);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       _barrier_spin_destroy  destroys  the barrier pointed to by
       barrier.  This includes invalidating the barrier and free-
       ing   any   associated   implementation-allocated  dynamic
       resources.

       Any user-allocated dynamic storage is unaffected by  _bar-
       rier_spin_destroy  and  must be explicitly released by the
       program.

   PPaarraammeetteerrss
       pointer to barrier to be destroyed

RReettuurrnn vvaalluueess
       _barrier_spin_destroy returns  zero  for  success  and  an
       error number for failure.

   EErrrroorrss
